#: src/philosophy.md:1
msgid "Our Philosophy"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:3
msgid ""
"Redox OS is predominately MIT X11-style licensed, including all software, "
"documentation, and fonts. There are only a few exceptions to this, which are "
"all licensed under other compatible open-source licenses."
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:5
msgid "The MIT X11-style license has the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:6
msgid ""
"It gives you, the user of the software, complete and unrestrained access to "
"the software, such that you may _inspect_, _modify_, and _redistribute_ your "
"changes"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:7
msgid ""
"_Inspection_ Anyone may inspect the software for security vulnerabilities"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:8
msgid ""
"_Modification_ Anyone may modify the software to fix security vulnerabilities"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:9
msgid ""
"_Redistribution_ Anyone may redistribute the software to patch the security "
"vulnerabilities"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:10
msgid ""
"It is compatible with GPL licenses - Projects licensed as GPL can be "
"distributed with Redox OS"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:11
msgid ""
"It allows for the incorporation of GPL-incompatible free software, such as "
"OpenZFS, which is CDDL licensed"
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:13
msgid ""
"The license does not restrict the software that may run on Redox, however -- "
"and thanks to the microkernel architecture, even traditionally tightly-"
"coupled components such as drivers can be distributed separately, so "
"maintainers are free to choose whatever license they like for their projects."
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:15
msgid ""
"This license was chosen to allow Redox to be used everywhere with minimum "
"restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:17
msgid ""
"Redox intends to be free forever, because we aim to be a foundational piece "
"in creating secure and resilient systems."
msgstr ""

#: src/philosophy.md:19
msgid ""
"Programs running on top of Redox don't have to be MIT X11-style licensed, "
"just like how other OSes do (e.g. proprietary programs and drivers on top of "
"Linux). But all of officially ported programs so far is only OSI and GNU "
"licensing compliant software."
msgstr ""
